[Mike] Hello, and welcome to the next session
of the WordPress Accessibility Day. I am your

00:00:14.700 --> 00:00:22.430
host, Mike Demo, and helping us in the chat
moderator, is Kayla Demopoulos. Our next session

00:00:22.430 --> 00:00:29.400
is going to be by Joe Hall. Joe has been a
WordPress developer and SEO for the last 11

00:00:29.400 --> 00:00:35.710
years. He first became interested in Accessibility
Consulting back in the 90s, but mostly does

00:00:35.710 --> 00:00:40.950
technical SEO for medium-sized companies,
non-profit, and enterprise-level brands. He

00:00:40.950 --> 00:00:49.610
is passionate about accessible, highly optimized,
and fast WordPress themes. Joe's talk is going

00:00:49.610 --> 00:00:56.260
to be about SEO and Web Accessibility: Partners
for a Better Internet. If you have any questions,

00:00:56.260 --> 00:01:02.100
please make sure to put them into the chat,
and we will get those at the end. And please

00:01:02.100 --> 00:01:06.420
remember that there is a code of conduct for
this event, and we're all part of the same

00:01:06.420 --> 00:01:17.780
WordPress community. Um, with that, thank
you so much, and welcome, Joe!

00:01:17.780 --> 00:01:32.020
[Joe Hall] I am looking forward to this conversation!
I'm gonna start my slides, here. Um, okay

00:01:32.020 --> 00:01:41.259
so uh this talk is called uh SEO and Web Accessibility:
Partners for a Better Internet.

00:01:41.259 --> 00:01:50.079
Um and I'm going to get started here. Okay,
so let's get started with some definitions.

00:01:50.079 --> 00:01:58.799
Uh this talk is geared towards uh folks that
are interested in SEO uh, but also for folks

00:01:58.799 --> 00:02:05.350
that are interested in accessibility obviously.
Um and so because we're talking to uh two

00:02:05.350 --> 00:02:12.900
separate uh groups, I thought it might be
smart to do some uh basic definitions, so

00:02:12.900 --> 00:02:22.190
that we're all on the same page. And so when
we talk about web accessibility, um web accessibility

00:02:22.190 --> 00:02:29.360
is the inclusive practice of ensuring there
is no barriers that prevent interaction with

00:02:29.360 --> 00:02:38.230
or access to websites on the world wide web,
for people with all types of disabilities.

00:02:38.230 --> 00:02:44.860
And when we talk about SEO, uh we're talking
about search engine optimization, uh the process

00:02:44.860 --> 00:02:52.650
of increasing the quality and quantity of
website traffic, by increasing the visibility

00:02:52.650 --> 00:03:01.320
of a website or web page to users of a web
search engine. This may involve increasing

00:03:01.320 --> 00:03:09.760
rankings found within the results, or improving
uh the presentation of existing listings or

00:03:09.760 --> 00:03:11.190
rankings.

00:03:11.190 --> 00:03:18.890
And you know, something, one of the really
interesting aspects of of SEO and web accessibility

00:03:18.890 --> 00:03:23.840
as a practice, if this is something you do
professionally, or you're just interested

00:03:23.840 --> 00:03:33.060
in it, um these two things can influence many
of the same areas of product development.

00:03:33.060 --> 00:03:41.540
So they both touch on User Experience, Design
and Information Architecture, Content Development,

00:03:41.540 --> 00:03:49.020
and Content Optimization and Technical Infrastructure
uh. So it makes sense that if there are so

00:03:49.020 --> 00:03:56.880
many overlapping areas that we should be working
closer together with each other um. It might

00:03:56.880 --> 00:04:02.750
be smart to go uh to dispel some myths uh,
because there are lots of myths around both

00:04:02.750 --> 00:04:09.320
practices um and it's smart to be on the same
page uh. So myth number one:

00:04:09.320 --> 00:04:14.710
Accessibility is only focused on improving
access for the visually impaired. I, I see

00:04:14.710 --> 00:04:22.319
a lot of SEOs with this uh, with this myth
and and the truth is that um accessibility

00:04:22.319 --> 00:04:29.340
is focused on lots of different types of disabilities:
Visual Impairments, Motor or Mobility Impairments,

00:04:29.340 --> 00:04:38.030
Auditory or Hearing Impairments, uh Seizure
Disorders, uh Cognitive or Intellectual disabilities.

00:04:38.030 --> 00:04:46.240
So we're talking about a cross disability
spectrum, not just visual impairments. Uh

00:04:46.240 --> 00:04:53.419
myth number two: SEO is only about optimizing
content uh with keywords. Um so this comes

00:04:53.419 --> 00:05:00.139
up a lot uh with with folks that have sort
of a cursory understanding of SEO, but the

00:05:00.139 --> 00:05:07.580
truth is that SEO follows uh technical best
practices. Um it looks at external signals

00:05:07.580 --> 00:05:15.189
such as, links or citations. It informs the
design or information architecture process

00:05:15.189 --> 00:05:22.289
and then of course it does focus on uh content
optimization. Another myth that I hear

00:05:22.289 --> 00:05:30.389
a lot of SEOs make is that: excellent SEO
means uh full accessibility or vice versa,

00:05:30.389 --> 00:05:36.840
and that full accessibility means excellent
SEO. And we'll take a look in this talk about

00:05:36.840 --> 00:05:45.219
how the two practices uh overlap each other
and how having good accessibility, can mean

00:05:45.219 --> 00:05:50.319
in some ways, that you do, when you're doing
the right thing for SEO, um and then vice

00:05:50.319 --> 00:05:57.680
versa with SEO for accessibility, but but
it's a it's a myth to assume that just because

00:05:57.680 --> 00:06:02.960
you have great accessibility that somehow
you're going to do really well with SEO. Or

00:06:02.960 --> 00:06:08.669
that just because you have great SEO, that
you know your website is accessible um. That's

00:06:08.669 --> 00:06:13.919
just not the case and we'll, we'll look into
that uh in a moment.

00:06:13.919 --> 00:06:20.039
So let's start talking about some of the areas
of overlap and conflict. I've put together

00:06:20.039 --> 00:06:27.289
a Venn diagram here and everything that's
listed on this diagram is of course not a

00:06:27.289 --> 00:06:32.400
complete list of either practice. This is
just an example of some of the things that

00:06:32.400 --> 00:06:40.479
might be found in each area and how some things
overlap. And on the uh on the left side, here

00:06:40.479 --> 00:06:49.449
I have SEO and in the SEO quadrant of this
Venn diagram I have listed: Page Speed, Structured

00:06:49.449 --> 00:06:59.050
Data, External Links, Mobile Indexing and
AMP? And then on the Accessibility only section

00:06:59.050 --> 00:07:09.360
of the Venn diagram I have: ARIA, Screen Readers,
HTML Landmarks, uh Keyboard Access, and Form

00:07:09.360 --> 00:07:17.669
Optimization. Some of the main, you know shared
areas, that overlap between SEO and Accessibility

00:07:17.669 --> 00:07:26.550
are: Information Architecture, uh we use some
Anchor Text, Content Optimization and Media

00:07:26.550 --> 00:07:33.569
Optimization. And so we'll take a look at
some of these overlapping areas now and see

00:07:33.569 --> 00:07:38.969
how they work together and how sometimes they
can cause conflicts as well.

00:07:38.969 --> 00:07:49.110
Um, so we'll start off with Information Architecture.
So with navigation items um you know, for

00:07:49.110 --> 00:07:56.550
SEO, navigation items should follow the information
architecture, have simple but descriptive

00:07:56.550 --> 00:08:03.599
labels and point to main sections of the site.
And you know for SEO, this is great, because

00:08:03.599 --> 00:08:09.729
uh these help build internal links uh site-wide,
which helps spread link equity and helps the

00:08:09.729 --> 00:08:16.961
search engines find all the main sections
of the site. For accessibility, navigation

00:08:16.961 --> 00:08:24.770
items should have a simple and descriptive
labels and this is, you know, primarily for

00:08:24.770 --> 00:08:34.310
ease of navigation and uh those navigation
items should be easy uh for the user to understand

00:08:34.310 --> 00:08:44.440
and find um easily. Unordered list, uh so
in HTML we have, you know, different types

00:08:44.440 --> 00:08:49.750
of lists. We have unordered lists and and
numbered list. Typically when we're making

00:08:49.750 --> 00:08:56.620
an information architecture or or navigation
uh, we'll use an unordered list um and then

00:08:56.620 --> 00:09:03.350
also, we'll use it also, for you know things
like tertiary navigation as well on the page.

00:09:03.350 --> 00:09:12.029
Um search engines prefer organized content
and clean HTML uh for navigation. So an unordered

00:09:12.029 --> 00:09:17.650
list is really great for search engines, because
they can easily understand that these links

00:09:17.650 --> 00:09:28.450
belong together as a set and they'll either
parse those um as uh parts of the featured

00:09:28.450 --> 00:09:34.019
snippet, if you're doing things like featured
snippet optimization um or other things.

00:09:34.019 --> 00:09:41.329
But for accessibility, uh screen readers will
parse unordered lists of links for menus.

00:09:41.329 --> 00:09:48.000
And so it's it's really helpful uh to think
about organizing, you know, your your navigation

00:09:48.000 --> 00:09:58.350
um especially sub-navigation or tertiary navigations
uh into unordered list, for both SEO and accessibility.

00:09:58.350 --> 00:10:04.190
Anchor Text: so this is our first item that
has a little bit of conflict uh. We'll start

00:10:04.190 --> 00:10:11.480
with the SEO part of it. Search engines use
anchor text uh to associate keywords within

00:10:11.480 --> 00:10:17.350
target pages that those links are linked to.
And so when we talk about anchor text, we're

00:10:17.350 --> 00:10:24.950
talking about the text found within a link
and so for SEO, uh search engines use that

00:10:24.950 --> 00:10:32.890
text to associate the terminology that should
be associated with the page that the link

00:10:32.890 --> 00:10:40.740
is pointing to. And then for accessibility,
uh screen readers will list links independently

00:10:40.740 --> 00:10:45.279
of content.
And therefore, anchor text should not rely

00:10:45.279 --> 00:10:51.839
on the context of the content um, it is found
in. So in other words, your anchor text should

00:10:51.839 --> 00:10:57.430
never be like, you know, click here, or you
know, download this. That kind of thing. Um

00:10:57.430 --> 00:11:03.680
it should always be descriptive of the page
that it's linking to, so that when those links

00:11:03.680 --> 00:11:10.069
are pulled out of the content and and made
into a independent navigation menu,

00:11:10.069 --> 00:11:17.759
it's easier to understand what those links
go to. Some conflicts. So SEOs have a tendency

00:11:17.759 --> 00:11:25.290
uh to stuff a bunch of keywords within uh
anchor text. Like I said before, it's because

00:11:25.290 --> 00:11:31.860
that anchor text can influence the terms that
the search engines will uh associate with

00:11:31.860 --> 00:11:37.420
that target page. And so you want to make
sure that as you are optimizing your anchor

00:11:37.420 --> 00:11:44.259
text, that that anchor text is also useful
for accessibility. You don't want to just

00:11:44.259 --> 00:11:50.709
jam up a bunch of keywords in your anchor
text so that when those links are taken out

00:11:50.709 --> 00:11:56.209
of the content mega menu, uh they still have
to make sense. Uh so it's really important

00:11:56.209 --> 00:12:04.230
for SEOs not to just jam up a bunch of keywords
into the anchor text and make for a bad navigation

00:12:04.230 --> 00:12:12.889
for screen readers. Let's go to Content Optimization.
So heading tags, you know, these are like

00:12:12.889 --> 00:12:21.899
your H1 H2, H3 tags uh for SEO they should
structure the content with main and sub-headings,

00:12:21.899 --> 00:12:29.091
uh use tags consecutively and include the
target terms. And generally you want to use

00:12:29.091 --> 00:12:31.259
like one H1

00:12:31.259 --> 00:12:36.850
tag per page and then underneath that use
consecutive order, you know, H2 H3 uh, H4,

00:12:36.850 --> 00:12:48.009
you know, uh down. For accessibility, uh screen
readers use uh these heading tags uh for content

00:12:48.009 --> 00:12:53.440
navigation um. And so you again, you wanna
use the same structure they would use for

00:12:53.440 --> 00:13:01.110
SEO um and use a very descriptive content
within the heading tags that would describe

00:13:01.110 --> 00:13:07.889
the content for that section of the page.
And so a good balance for SEO and accessibility,

00:13:07.889 --> 00:13:14.500
is that you know, you you can label the these
heading tags with content that includes,

00:13:14.500 --> 00:13:25.550
you know, descriptive keywords that also describe
uh the content that um the headings represent.

00:13:25.550 --> 00:13:33.769
Title Tags: so title tags are a very important
part of SEO um and so title tag should include

00:13:33.769 --> 00:13:41.100
unique targeting keywords for rankings of
an increase, increased clickthrough rates.

00:13:41.100 --> 00:13:47.920
For accessibility, title tags should include
unique terms for navigation. Um, now a conflict

00:13:47.920 --> 00:13:52.339
that I
see sometimes is that SEO sometimes include

00:13:52.339 --> 00:13:59.660
uh marketing language in the content in the
title tags, uh such as clickthrough, uh calls

00:13:59.660 --> 00:14:05.470
to action, to increase clickthrough rates.
And so basically the the reasons this happens

00:14:05.470 --> 00:14:13.000
is, because uh the search snippet, the what
you see within the search results, that title

00:14:13.000 --> 00:14:20.750
there is taken from a title tag and so SEOs
oftentimes like to write kind of eye-popping

00:14:20.750 --> 00:14:27.750
marketing language within the title tag to
get users to click on uh their search result,

00:14:27.750 --> 00:14:35.279
within the search rankings um.
And that's fine, but a problem with that is

00:14:35.279 --> 00:14:42.180
that, that can get in the way of providing
a useful navigation item. If you think about

00:14:42.180 --> 00:14:50.760
title tags as sort of a way to navigate through
the pages, either through using tabs on your

00:14:50.760 --> 00:14:58.120
browser, or navigation within a list of bookmarks,
that kind of thing, you should always kind

00:14:58.120 --> 00:15:03.930
of keep your title tags um as easy to understand
as possible. And you can find a good balance

00:15:03.930 --> 00:15:10.500
between having a good call to action, but
also making it so it's, you know, kind of

00:15:10.500 --> 00:15:19.930
concise and easy to understand that's the
best method. Um, so Keywords and Language:

00:15:19.930 --> 00:15:27.990
so you want to use keywords for SEO of in
a natural way. You know historically SEOs

00:15:27.990 --> 00:15:31.939
have been kind of notorious about, you know,

00:15:31.939 --> 00:15:38.170
pumping a bunch of keywords in the content
and trying to kind of force their content

00:15:38.170 --> 00:15:45.560
into those results.That's no longer as popular
anymore as it used to be, which is a good

00:15:45.560 --> 00:15:51.660
thing, because for accessibility, content
should adhere to good readability standards

00:15:51.660 --> 00:15:57.610
and should be easily understood. These two
things really go together in my mind, because

00:15:57.610 --> 00:16:03.990
uh the search engines are starting to employ
more and more natural language processing

00:16:03.990 --> 00:16:12.139
which attempts to understand the content the
way a human being would read it. And so therefore,

00:16:12.139 --> 00:16:19.209
you know, using a bunch of targeted keywords,
uh and writing your content in a way that

00:16:19.209 --> 00:16:26.209
doesn''t sound natural,
may be not so smart for either SEO or accessibility.

00:16:26.209 --> 00:16:32.810
So it's always good to use natural language
and to use content that that makes sense both

00:16:32.810 --> 00:16:42.189
for all users, you know, search engines and
uh human beings. Hidden Content: so I saw

00:16:42.189 --> 00:16:50.860
this mentioned earlier today um in someone's
uh talk and for SEO, hidden content is not

00:16:50.860 --> 00:16:59.470
detected by search engines. And in some cases
it can be a violation of their quality guidelines.

00:16:59.470 --> 00:17:10.429
In accessibility, you can hide content from
visual users um, but then make it accessible

00:17:10.429 --> 00:17:15.539
to screen readers um, And so there's different
reasons why you might want to do this. So

00:17:15.539 --> 00:17:22.159
for example, you might have a completely separate
navigation just for screen readers, but you

00:17:22.159 --> 00:17:30.040
don't want that navigation to be visible to
users, you know, visual users. And that's

00:17:30.040 --> 00:17:37.010
understandable, but accessibility professionals
should not hide content that is critical for

00:17:37.010 --> 00:17:43.820
SEO. And this is just kind of common sense
in a way, because if we follow the principles

00:17:43.820 --> 00:17:49.711
of
universal design, then we are making all of

00:17:49.711 --> 00:17:57.440
the content, you know, kind of equally accessible
to all different users. And so, you know,

00:17:57.440 --> 00:18:03.240
if there's a special case where okay you have
to hide a certain navigation just for screen

00:18:03.240 --> 00:18:08.390
readers,
that's understandable uh, but if you are hiding

00:18:08.390 --> 00:18:15.060
content just for screen readers and some of
that content has links in it that is not available

00:18:15.060 --> 00:18:24.270
to the visual users, then those links are
not going to be uh used for SEO. So just keep

00:18:24.270 --> 00:18:29.260
in mind that, you know, when you're hiding
content, you need to keep things equal on

00:18:29.260 --> 00:18:35.240
both ends. You know, that same content that
maybe is hidden from visual users needs to

00:18:35.240 --> 00:18:41.409
be kind of represented in some way um especially
internal links, because those are very important

00:18:41.409 --> 00:18:52.830
for SEO. So Media Optimization: so one of
the things that SEOs talk about whenever uh

00:18:52.830 --> 00:19:03.480
accessibility comes up is alt tags for images
um. And SEOs tend to like to optimize alt

00:19:03.480 --> 00:19:14.080
text for images, because search engines utilize
the text found in um alt attributes uh to

00:19:14.080 --> 00:19:22.799
associate keywords for an understanding of
the image. And so I, I think initially when

00:19:22.799 --> 00:19:27.751
search engines started doing this, it was
a really great idea, because you know if you

00:19:27.751 --> 00:19:33.640
use the alt tags the way they're supposed
to be, then you will include a very descriptive

00:19:33.640 --> 00:19:40.960
um description of the image. And so obviously
the search engines thought, oh we can just

00:19:40.960 --> 00:19:46.250
take those out and we'll know what the image
is then. Um and I think that's true still

00:19:46.250 --> 00:19:53.000
today. However, one of the conflicts I found
is that SEOs generally don't write very good

00:19:53.000 --> 00:20:02.970
alt text. They just stuff the alt text full
of keywords. And I've actually noticed where

00:20:02.970 --> 00:20:09.470
it's become a common place in WordPress, to
basically just take, like the title of the

00:20:09.470 --> 00:20:16.960
post, and pop that into the image alt text
or, or even if it's, if you're using something

00:20:16.960 --> 00:20:23.149
like WooCommerce,
sometimes they'll take like the product name

00:20:23.149 --> 00:20:29.600
and put that into the alt text of uh the product
image. Um in some cases that stuff works,

00:20:29.600 --> 00:20:33.680
but but if you're if you're a blogger and,
you know, you're writing about something,

00:20:33.680 --> 00:20:39.150
you have an image in your article, it's likely
that the title of the blog post is not going

00:20:39.150 --> 00:20:44.820
to match up with a description of the image
that you're posting. Uh so it's really important

00:20:44.820 --> 00:20:51.540
not to do that kind of stuff, and it's a really
easy way I think to optimize the alt text,

00:20:51.540 --> 00:20:57.940
because, you know, if you have like 200 images
that are missing alt text, it's super easy

00:20:57.940 --> 00:21:07.120
just to go in and change your uh WordPress
theme to do that, but in the end it doesn't

00:21:07.120 --> 00:21:14.200
really serve uh your user, your users that
use screen readers uh very much at all. Um

00:21:14.200 --> 00:21:19.760
and oftentimes, it actually doesn't really
provide much value for SEO either uh, because

00:21:19.760 --> 00:21:25.690
they're not really a good description of the
image at all either uh. So, you know, it is

00:21:25.690 --> 00:21:30.860
kind of a pain in the butt, but it's always
better to write your own alt text by hand

00:21:30.860 --> 00:21:41.010
and not try to optimize it or or or automate
it. Videos: so I see a lot of folks that do

00:21:41.010 --> 00:21:49.460
videos and the obvious accessibility approach
to videos is to include uh closed captioning.

00:21:49.460 --> 00:21:58.570
Um and closed captioning is, has become relatively
more accepted, and a lot easier to implement.

00:21:58.570 --> 00:22:07.370
I watch different platforms um. For SEO, what
you can do is, you can take the same transcript

00:22:07.370 --> 00:22:13.750
of, for the closed captions and utilize that
for SEO content. Uh so you can put that on

00:22:13.750 --> 00:22:20.090
the same page as the video. If you have an
embedded video, you can totally just take

00:22:20.090 --> 00:22:25.809
the closed captioning content uh and then
put that on the same page as a, you know,

00:22:25.809 --> 00:22:30.659
video transcript.
And that turns into a really great optimized,

00:22:30.659 --> 00:22:38.650
SEO friendly content for the video um. And
the same thing for podcasts. You can, you

00:22:38.650 --> 00:22:44.780
can do the same thing for podcasts. Podcasts
are very popular now. Uh if you have an audio

00:22:44.780 --> 00:22:55.070
transcript, that can be placed on the same
page um as uh the podcast is embedded in.

00:22:55.070 --> 00:23:02.350
And that creates a really great thing for
SEO um and also for screen readers that would

00:23:02.350 --> 00:23:12.400
just read the uh audio transcript that's on
the page where the podcast um is embedded.

00:23:12.400 --> 00:23:19.510
Um so that wraps up the majority of uh this
talk and the talk went a little faster than

00:23:19.510 --> 00:23:26.039
I anticipated, but I do have some closing
thoughts. So the best way to optimize for

00:23:26.039 --> 00:23:35.140
both accessibility and SEO is to work alongside
amazing professionals that specialize in each.

00:23:35.140 --> 00:23:44.600
And I really can't stress this enough, because
I feel like um SEO and accessibility, because

00:23:44.600 --> 00:23:52.019
it touches on so many different areas and
because uh each one of the practices uh can

00:23:52.019 --> 00:24:00.480
be very detail-oriented and very specific
to different types of websites, or are very

00:24:00.480 --> 00:24:07.080
specific and different types of clients, it's
really difficult to be a Jack or or Jane of

00:24:07.080 --> 00:24:17.000
all trades and do both. Uh so I would encourage
everyone to make friends uh with an SEO or

00:24:17.000 --> 00:24:24.140
an accessibility professional, and encourage
them to work alongside you, and and develop

00:24:24.140 --> 00:24:32.520
projects together and share in your own experience
um to to build uh better products. Of course,

00:24:32.520 --> 00:24:40.399
you can both learn about each other's, you
know, fields and and do the best you can,

00:24:40.399 --> 00:24:45.039
but it's really important to have someone
that really knows what they're doing um and

00:24:45.039 --> 00:24:46.270
with lots of experience.

00:24:46.270 --> 00:24:55.299
My name is Joe Hall and you can reach me at
these websites and at the end here I've included

00:24:55.299 --> 00:25:01.890
some more reading for the SEO folks. Here's
some further read on accessibility. And then

