00:33:01.430 --> 00:33:07.679
in the time stamps for it um. So I think a
good balance between the automated and me

00:33:07.679 --> 00:33:15.120
uh and the human kind of uh approach is best,
you know. Yeah.

00:33:15.120 --> 00:33:19.889
[Mike] Sure um yeah, you know get the head
start on the automated stuff and then clean

00:33:19.889 --> 00:33:25.899
it up a little bit yourself. Excellent. Another
question we got on the chat is: How important

00:33:25.899 --> 00:33:29.990
is alt attributes in SEO ranking and accessibility?

00:33:29.990 --> 00:33:37.250
So it's important for uh for SEO. It's important
for image search. So when you go to Google

00:33:37.250 --> 00:33:43.470
and you go to the Google image search and
you, you know, type a questionnaire or some

00:33:43.470 --> 00:33:49.350
keywords you get a bunch of images. Uh that's
how Google ranks those images, is by using

00:33:49.350 --> 00:33:57.789
alt text and then also the text found around
the image. Um and so for SEO, that that's

00:33:57.789 --> 00:34:03.799
what, that's really important.
Uh but for uh accessibility, obviously uh

00:34:03.799 --> 00:34:10.659
that's very important for uh screen readers
and, you know, like I mentioned before, um

00:34:10.659 --> 00:34:16.020
having a good balance between the two is important.
Um I really think it's important to maybe

00:34:16.020 --> 00:34:21.500
go the accessibility route more when doing
alt text. Uh and if you're able to throw in

00:34:21.500 --> 00:34:26.300
some keywords that's great uh, but at the
end of the day you don't want to just jam

00:34:26.300 --> 00:34:33.369
a bunch of keywords into the alt text, because
that's not really good accessibility, at all.

00:34:33.369 --> 00:34:39.139
And and honestly it's not really good for
SEO either. SEO needs to be natural language,

00:34:39.139 --> 00:34:45.869
needs to have, make sense to human beings
and and search crawlers, you know. [Mike]

00:34:45.869 --> 00:34:50.609
Yeah and I know Twitter, I believe, just launched
