maybe it's better for all users that it stay
visible?

00:35:31.260 --> 00:35:38.740
[Joe] Uh I'm not sure I understand the last
part of that question. [Mike] Yeah, so I'm

00:35:38.740 --> 00:35:45.240
not exactly sure on the context here. I kind
of just read it. So, maybe there is uh a user

00:35:45.240 --> 00:35:51.540
interface that maybe some text is hidden unless
there's a certain element um engaged with,

00:35:51.540 --> 00:35:55.290
versus maybe showing that uh text at the first.

00:35:55.290 --> 00:35:58.619
[Joe] Okay, yeah yeah I understand now. So
for SEO

00:35:58.619 --> 00:36:08.319
um Google's crawlers uh utilize Chrome. So
they actually, like Google's crawlers actually

00:36:08.319 --> 00:36:15.000
is based on Chrome now um and so what it does
is it it renders the page as if it's being

00:36:15.000 --> 00:36:22.950
opened in Chrome.
However, it does not utilize a mouse uh. So

00:36:22.950 --> 00:36:30.040
user interface interaction um does not really
help with the SEO, so so content is hidden

00:36:30.040 --> 00:36:37.970
behind a a tab or a module or or something
that requires you know like user interface,

00:36:37.970 --> 00:36:46.450
a user interaction, um SEO or search engines
will not see it. Now this is actually a a

00:36:46.450 --> 00:36:53.410
kind of a debated topic among SEO nerds um,
but generally speaking we have to go with

00:36:53.410 --> 00:37:00.300
what Google says and they say they don't,
you know uh they don't surface content that's

00:37:00.300 --> 00:37:07.570
not you know visible without um without user
interaction. Now that being said, like you

00:37:07.570 --> 00:37:16.160
know, screen readers for example, um a lot
of websites hide uh separate navigations just

00:37:16.160 --> 00:37:24.369
for screen readers. Um and I think that that
that's fine um, you know, if if you are hiding

00:37:24.369 --> 00:37:31.780
content that's that's just for screen readers
uh, just make sure it's the same content that

00:37:31.780 --> 00:37:38.690
would be needed for SEO. Well you know, you
don't want to hide anything that could have

00:37:38.690 --> 00:37:46.359
value from an SEO perspective. Um you want
to keep everything kind of visible um and

00:37:46.359 --> 00:37:52.230
you know so that search engines can parse
it and utilize it, you know, in a visual format.

00:37:52.230 --> 00:37:59.700
[Mike] Uh certainly. Another question we got
is: How do you prioritize to give focus to

