00:38:39.990 --> 00:38:46.690
So one thing that you can, it obviously is
different for every client, right. So some

00:38:46.690 --> 00:38:52.800
clients are going to be more flexible and
be willing to change uh for SEO uh. Some clients

00:38:52.800 --> 00:39:00.990
are not. Um I think what you need to do as
a professional is, on your own time, prioritize

00:39:00.990 --> 00:39:06.589
what's worth uh fighting for and what's what's
not worth fighting for um. Some things you

00:39:06.589 --> 00:39:12.230
need to understand that, you know that it's
the right thing to do, but really is it going

00:39:12.230 --> 00:39:16.430
to move a needle for SEO? Probably not,

00:39:16.430 --> 00:39:23.920
so you don't really need to argue about it
with your client, you know. Um you can uh

00:39:23.920 --> 00:39:29.500
in some cases, and I do this a lot, in some
cases you can try to convince your client

00:39:29.500 --> 00:39:37.359
to create a whole different piece of content.
Like I say, okay you can keep this, you know,

00:39:37.359 --> 00:39:43.920
because a lot of times clients like to have
pages for things like paid search or social,

00:39:43.920 --> 00:39:48.740
uh channels, that kind of stuff and that and
those things just don't work with SEO content

00:39:48.740 --> 00:39:54.920
and so you can say okay we can keep these
pages to use for advertising and that kind

00:39:54.920 --> 00:40:02.760
of thing, but let's create like a a sister
page that covers the same topics, but is well

00:40:02.760 --> 00:40:06.490
optimized for SEO. Um and that usually works
out really well,

00:40:06.490 --> 00:40:11.250
because then you can focus all your time and
priority on what we call, we call those like

00:40:11.250 --> 00:40:17.750
SEO landing pages. Focus all your time and
priority and SEO kind of uh perspective on

00:40:17.750 --> 00:40:23.900
those pages and they get to keep, you know,
their other content um and do whatever they

00:40:23.900 --> 00:40:26.420
want with it, you know.

00:40:26.420 --> 00:40:32.730
[Mike] Sure, and our last question is: What
